text: Year 33 BC was either a common year starting on Saturday, Sunday or Monday or a leap year starting on Sunday of the Julian calendar. At the time, it was known as the Year of the Consulship of Octavian and Tullus. == Events == * Mark Antony annexed the kingdom of Media * The Kinambroi surrendered to Octavian * Crown Prince Ao ascends the throne in China as Emperor Cheng of Han == Deaths == * Tiberius Nero, father of Tiberius (b. c. 85 BC) * Emperor Yuan of Han (b. 75 BC) Category:30s BC
title: 33 BC
